        "content": "<h3>Q1</h3>\n\n<p>df shows 100% usage.</p>\n\n<p>du only shows 50%.</p>\n\n<p>Why?</p>\n\n<p>Expected Answer<br>예상 답변</p>\n\n<p>Deleted files may still be held open by processes.</p>\n\n<p>Investigate using:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">lsof | grep deleted</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Q2</h3>\n\n<p>Filesystem has free space but applications cannot create files.</p>\n\n<p>Why?</p>\n\n<p>Expected Answer<br>예상 답변</p>\n\n<p>Possible inode exhaustion.</p>\n\n<p>Check:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">df -i</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Q3</h3>\n\n<p>How would you identify the largest files?</p>\n\n<p>Expected Answer<br>예상 답변</p>\n\n<p>Use:</p>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">du -ah / | sort -rh</code></pre>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Q4</h3>\n\n<p>What is an inode?</p>\n\n<p>Expected Answer<br>예상 답변</p>\n\n<p>Metadata structure describing files and directories.</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<h3>Q5</h3>\n\n<p>How would you prevent future disk-full incidents?</p>\n\n<p>Expected Answer<br>예상 답변</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Log rotation</li>\n<li>Retention policies</li>\n<li>Monitoring alerts</li>\n<li>Capacity planning</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr>"
